# [ANRW](../wg/anrw.html)

## Summary

The Applied Networking Research Workshop (ANRW) was held as a joint workshop of the IRTF and ACM. The session opened with administrative remarks, noting that the Note Well applies and outlining submission statistics: 61 submissions were received (48 long papers, 13 short papers), resulting in 26 accepted papers (20 long, 6 short) organized into topic-specific sessions. 

The workshop featured a keynote presentation on the critical transitions of the Internet and its interaction with power grid security, followed by a session on Network Management. This first session covered topics including unified network abstraction via knowledge graphs, state transfer latency reduction in edge clouds, dynamic segment sizing for congestion control, zero-copy Layer 7 load balancing, and predictive queuing in mobile edge networks.

